Security scanner for AUR packages

Usage: aur-scan [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  scan     Scan a PKGBUILD file or directory
  check    Check an AUR package BEFORE installation (fetches from AUR)
  install  Race-free install: scan the exact bytes, then build them in dep order
  system   Scan all installed AUR packages on the system
  rules    List available detection rules
  explain  Explain a detection code in detail
  codes    List all detection codes with brief descriptions
  ioc      Show or query the IOC (indicator of compromise) database
  version  Check scanner version and configuration
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -c, --config <CONFIG>      Configuration file path
  -s, --severity <SEVERITY>  Minimum severity to report [possible values: critical, high, medium, low, info]
  -v, --verbose              Enable verbose output
  -q, --quiet                Quiet mode (only show findings)
  -h, --help                 Print help
  -V, --version              Print version
